http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: The Economic Standards describe what students should know and be able to do in third through twelfth grade. They reflect the increasing complexity and sophistication that students are expected to achieve as they progress through school. The document attempts to avoid repetition and to show a progression across grade levels.
